---
/*
  DIY subpage 4 of 4 — How to Host a Closing Exhibition
  (/diy/host-an-exhibition). The last page in the read-in-order set.

  Sections, top to bottom (ticker, masthead, footer come from BaseLayout):
    1. Hero       — the M ❀ logo
    2. Heading    — cyan "* HOW TO HOST A CLOSING EXHIBITION" bar
    3. Body       — blue sub-headings, the offtime-outlets graphic, a Vimeo
                    embed of the Month Offline Gallery, and two photos
    4. Next       — loops back to the DIY guide index (no forward arrow)

  Underlined words use plain <u> for emphasis (same as the other subpages).
---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import NextLink from '../../components/NextLink.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Host a Closing Exhibition — Month Offline" masthead="Month Offline > DIY Guide > Exhibition">
  <div class="sections">
    <!-- 1. Hero -->
    <Hero />

    <!-- 2. Heading -->
    <SectionHeader label="How to host a closing exhibition" />

    <!-- 3. Body -->
    <section class="card">
      <h3 class="label">Offtime outlets</h3>
      <p class="body">
        Month Offline is not just about what we're saying no to, but what we're
        inviting in. We ask participants to consider choosing an Offtime Outlet
        for the month. How might they want to spend their newfound time? This is
        a permission slip to do that thing they've always wanted to do. Keep it
        low-stakes and low-pressure! Offtime outlets come in many different
        shapes and sizes (including napping and spending more time with your
        kids). Set aside some time to chat about offtime at each MO meetup.
      </p>

      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/exhibition-01.png"
        width="1200"
        height="1800"
        alt="A handwritten Offtime Outlets sign-up sheet listing participants and the slow pursuits they chose"
      />

      <h3 class="label">Celebrate good times</h3>
      <p class="body">
        The original Month Offline cohorts in DC and NYC ended with a public,
        phone-free exhibition where participants shared the offtime projects they
        worked on with friends, family, and neighbors.
      </p>

      <!-- Vimeo embed of the Month Offline Gallery video. The responsive
           wrapper below keeps it at a 16:9 ratio at any width. -->
      <div class="video">
        <iframe
          src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1153751486"
          title="Month Offline Gallery"
          allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"
          allowfullscreen
        ></iframe>
      </div>

      <p class="body">
        The exhibition feels sort of like a science fair for adults. Spread the
        word by printing physical invitations and submitting to local newspapers
        or community calendars.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        Invite 2-3 participants to share their experience during a ~20min
        fireside chat and give the guests plenty of time to ask their own
        questions. It's always a good time to hear the trials and triumphs from
        the month-long challenge. People are always inspired to join a future
        cohort! Find a way to record their contact information so you can follow
        up with them after the event.
      </p>

      <h3 class="label">The dumb scroll</h3>
      <p class="body">
        At the exhibition, we unveil and unroll a "finite" scroll -- a
        collective art piece made up of drawings that participants create at each
        meetup. It's an analog form of social media that allows us to create
        "content" for each other while we're offline. You can do it too! You'll
        just need some butcher paper and some sharpies.
      </p>

      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/exhibition-02.png"
        width="1500"
        height="1000"
        alt="A crowd gathered outdoors around the unrolled dumb scroll"
      />
      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/exhibition-03.png"
        width="1500"
        height="1000"
        alt="Guests viewing the dumb scroll displayed on a wall at the indoor exhibition"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Next — last page loops back to the DIY guide index (no arrow). -->
    <NextLink label="DIY Guide" href="/diy" arrow={false} />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Standard body paragraph (Syne Mono). */
  .body {
    font-size: var(--size-body);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }
  .body + .body {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  /* Blue sub-headings inside the card (same as the home page's "How it works"). */
  .label {
    font-size: var(--size-body);
    color: var(--mo-blue);
    letter-spacing: var(--track-label);
  }
  .label + .body {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  /* Photos interspersed through the card. */
  .card__photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
  }

  /* Responsive 16:9 wrapper for the Vimeo embed. The iframe fills it
     absolutely so the box keeps its ratio at any column width. */
  .video {
    position: relative;
    padding-top: 56.25%; /* 9 / 16 = 0.5625 */
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
  }
  .video iframe {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
  }
</style>
